uk.ac.ed.epcc.webapp.forms.transition

Interface IndexTransitionFactory<K,T>

  • Type Parameters:
    K -
    T -
    All Superinterfaces:
    Contexed, TransitionFactory<K,T>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    IndexTransitionProvider<K,T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicFormTransitionProvider, FormFactoryProviderTransitionProvider, PersonalResponseTransitionProvider, PreferenceTransitionProvider, TableTransitionProvider

    public interface IndexTransitionFactory<K,T>
extends TransitionFactory<K,T>
    TransitionProvider that can generate a default transition i.e. a TargetLessTransition for selecting a target or a navigation transition to an index page. It can also be used to supply a default transition for a target. An Index transition should usually not modify state. Consider having the key implement ViewTransitionKey
    See Also:
    DefaultingTransitionFactory
